## Spell Descriptions

| Spell | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `/@NAMESPACE@idiomatic` | Modifier | Set session constraints to use canonical, documented patterns for a tool or language |
| `/@NAMESPACE@socratic` | Modifier | Shift the AI into Socratic teaching mode — questions instead of answers |
| `/@NAMESPACE@bpap` | Workflow | Research and produce a structured best-practices and antipatterns document for a topic |
| `/@NAMESPACE@progressive-disclosure` | Workflow | Break documentation into linked, AI-friendly files at progressive detail levels |
| `/@NAMESPACE@diataxis` | Workflow | Generate or audit documentation using the four-quadrant Diataxis framework |
| `/@NAMESPACE@task-graph` | Workflow | Map task dependencies or diagram a workflow using DAGs and critical path analysis |
| `/@NAMESPACE@debug` | Workflow | Systematic root cause analysis — find the real bug before attempting fixes |
| `/@NAMESPACE@deep-dive` | Workflow | Explore and map how a codebase or subsystem works — architecture, data flow, and key abstractions |
| `/@NAMESPACE@teach` | Meta | Learn the real-world concept behind any spell — where it comes from, where you see it, how the spell applies it |
| `/@NAMESPACE@help` | Meta | Show this listing, or detailed help for a specific spell |

